Description:
    Sets up Kamal deployment configuration for your Oroshi application.

    This generator will:
    - Create Kamal deploy configuration (config/deploy.yml)
    - Create Dockerfile for production builds
    - Create .dockerignore for efficient builds
    - Create secrets template (.kamal/secrets-example)
    - Create database setup SQL (db/production_setup.sql)
    - Create Docker entrypoint script (bin/docker-entrypoint)
    - Create pre-build hook for quality checks (.kamal/hooks/pre-build)
    - Create environment variables example (.env.example)

Example:
    rails generate oroshi:deployment \
      --domain=oroshi.example.com \
      --host=192.168.1.100

    This will create:
        config/deploy.yml
        Dockerfile
        .dockerignore
        .kamal/secrets-example
        .kamal/hooks/pre-build
        bin/docker-entrypoint
        db/production_setup.sql
        .env.example

Options:
    --domain=DOMAIN        Your application domain (e.g., oroshi.example.com)
    --host=HOST            SSH host/IP for deployment (e.g., 192.168.1.100)
    --registry=REGISTRY    Docker registry (default: docker.io, or AWS ECR URL)
    --skip-dockerfile      Skip Dockerfile generation
    --skip-secrets         Skip secrets file generation

After running this generator:
    1. Copy and configure secrets:
       cp .kamal/secrets-example .kamal/secrets
       # Edit .kamal/secrets with your credentials

    2. Set environment variables:
       export KAMAL_HOST=your.server.ip.address
       export KAMAL_DOMAIN=your-domain.com

    3. Setup server (first time):
       kamal setup

    4. Deploy application:
       kamal deploy

    5. Monitor deployment:
       kamal app logs -f
       kamal app logs --roles workers -f

For more information:
    - See CLAUDE.md for comprehensive deployment guide
    - Visit https://kamal-deploy.org for Kamal documentation
